WEBVTT

00:00:49.776 --> 00:00:51.443
-Henna?
-Yes?

00:00:51.443 --> 00:00:54.526
-Can you fix my hair?
-Okay.

00:01:00.818 --> 00:01:04.443
Hi! What's up?

00:01:06.110 --> 00:01:07.235
I'm at a shoot.

00:01:08.026 --> 00:01:09.526
No, I can talk.

00:01:09.818 --> 00:01:11.318
They're setting up the lighting.
Just a minute.

00:01:14.526 --> 00:01:16.485
It's an old house in North Calcutta.

00:01:18.485 --> 00:01:19.318
"Lingering Doubt".

00:01:20.068 --> 00:01:24.693
Come on, not lingerie! 'Lingering'...okay?

00:01:25.485 --> 00:01:27.193
It's a serious film, dude!

00:01:28.901 --> 00:01:29.693
Today?

00:01:29.901 --> 00:01:32.693
No, there's a premiere party today.

00:01:33.068 --> 00:01:36.443
As if your picture never gets printed on page 3!

00:01:37.485 --> 00:01:38.443
Tomorrow?

00:01:39.443 --> 00:01:40.485
Hold on...

00:01:40.776 --> 00:01:42.235
-Henna?
-Yes?

00:01:42.235 --> 00:01:44.693
-Please hand me my diary.
-Yes.

00:01:45.068 --> 00:01:46.985
Ma'am, the shot is ready.

00:01:47.151 --> 00:01:52.401
You are admiring the necklace
in front of the mirror.

00:01:52.610 --> 00:01:54.235
The trolley will follow you.

00:01:54.318 --> 00:01:55.818
You should look quite happy and mushy.

00:01:55.860 --> 00:01:57.818
-Shall we go for a rehearsal?
-Yeah, yeah, please.

00:01:57.985 --> 00:01:58.818
Trolley.

00:01:59.776 --> 00:02:00.818
Silence!

00:02:00.860 --> 00:02:02.818
Go on, go on...that's it.

00:02:03.068 --> 00:02:04.318
This is the last mark.

00:02:04.776 --> 00:02:06.026
-Okay?
-Yes.

00:02:06.026 --> 00:02:06.401
DIRECTOR: DEBABRATA RAY.

00:02:06.401 --> 00:02:08.318
"Lingering Doubt"
Scene 12, shot one, take one.

00:02:09.568 --> 00:02:10.818
Action!

00:02:21.568 --> 00:02:23.068
Hey hey, hey!

00:02:23.943 --> 00:02:26.068
-What happened?
-Get some water!

00:02:29.193 --> 00:02:31.276
Welcome back after the break.
I'm Shonali...

00:02:31.276 --> 00:02:36.026
Bringing you hot news and gossip
from the world of entertainment...

00:02:36.026 --> 00:02:37.901
on your favorite program Shooting Star.

00:02:37.901 --> 00:02:42.526
A very strange incident took place last week
during the shooting of the film "Lingering Doubt."

00:02:42.901 --> 00:02:47.818
The lead actress of the film Madhumita
suddenly fainted in the middle of a shot.

00:02:48.068 --> 00:02:54.318
Apparenly, she saw the reflection of an
unfamiliar woman in the mirror.

00:02:54.443 --> 00:02:56.443
Who was this mysterious woman?

00:02:56.776 --> 00:02:59.568
Did Madhumita see a ghost?

00:03:00.610 --> 00:03:03.318
PRESENTED BY SATYA FILMS
AND MOJO PRODUCTION

00:03:04.026 --> 00:03:06.318
ANIK DUTTA'S MOTION PICTURE

00:03:07.110 --> 00:03:11.026
THE FUTURE OF THE PAST

00:03:16.276 --> 00:03:19.610
Excess in the name of progress

00:03:19.901 --> 00:03:23.276
Bulldozers are razing all the old houses

00:03:23.276 --> 00:03:25.276
Gone, gone, everything's gone

00:03:26.985 --> 00:03:30.526
High rises, multiplexes and shopping malls

00:03:30.526 --> 00:03:34.110
Promoters are taking over all the land

00:03:34.110 --> 00:03:37.568
Calcutta is now a concrete jungle

00:03:37.693 --> 00:03:41.026
Heritage is disappearing fast

00:03:48.360 --> 00:03:51.818
As the old houses disappear

00:03:51.901 --> 00:03:55.235
ghosts are in great trouble

00:03:55.443 --> 00:03:58.943
No one is concerned about them

00:03:58.985 --> 00:04:02.526
The future of the ghosts is doomed

00:04:02.526 --> 00:04:05.860
Silent are the intellectuals

00:04:06.110 --> 00:04:09.443
The civil society is also indifferent

00:04:16.735 --> 00:04:20.276
The administration is quiet

00:04:20.276 --> 00:04:23.610
Same with the media and the opposition

00:04:23.860 --> 00:04:27.276
No hunger strikes or demonstrations

00:04:27.401 --> 00:04:30.943
Because ghosts are not voters

00:04:30.985 --> 00:04:34.485
Where will all the ghosts go?

00:04:34.526 --> 00:04:38.151
This film was made to protest against all this

00:04:59.526 --> 00:05:01.901
There, park in front of that gate ahead.

00:05:11.235 --> 00:05:12.568
What a house!

00:05:13.193 --> 00:05:15.651
But it's not that well-maintained.

00:05:16.610 --> 00:05:19.068
That's what happens
with disputed properties.

00:05:19.860 --> 00:05:23.568
But I guess they've renovated the interiors
since people shoot films here.

00:05:23.943 --> 00:05:27.443
It's been closed for almost a year.

00:05:28.901 --> 00:05:31.860
Remember the Madhumita incident?

00:05:31.860 --> 00:05:32.610
Which incident?

00:05:32.860 --> 00:05:33.943
Oh, the "ghost" affair?

00:05:35.151 --> 00:05:36.068
Just imagine!

00:05:36.193 --> 00:05:37.651
Yeah, Sudhir?
Yeah, yeah.

00:05:37.901 --> 00:05:38.860
This is Nantu speaking.

00:05:39.235 --> 00:05:41.276
Yes, we've already reached.

00:05:42.318 --> 00:05:46.485
Sir, we production managers are
extremely punctual.

00:05:46.651 --> 00:05:47.985
Let me see.

00:05:48.318 --> 00:05:50.776
Okay, we'll wait.

00:05:51.901 --> 00:05:53.776
Is Madhumita going
through such a PR crisis?

00:05:54.610 --> 00:05:55.943
Why such cheap publicity?

00:05:56.068 --> 00:05:57.776
Well, whatever it was, it worked.

00:05:57.985 --> 00:06:00.151
Check out the TV channels, newspapers...

00:06:00.151 --> 00:06:02.110
Ghosts intrigue everyone!

00:06:03.235 --> 00:06:04.610
It's great for publicity.

00:06:04.693 --> 00:06:06.360
Hence, the popularity
of ghost stories!

00:06:06.360 --> 00:06:07.693
Yes, numerous films too.

00:06:08.526 --> 00:06:12.943
But what about the caretaker?

00:06:12.943 --> 00:06:15.610
He is just about to reach.

00:06:15.860 --> 00:06:17.943
A round of tea, meanwhile?

00:06:18.110 --> 00:06:20.985
A shop nearby makes awesome tea.

00:06:21.068 --> 00:06:21.901
We'll do all that later.

00:06:23.068 --> 00:06:25.610
Is that your caretaker "framing" in?

00:06:26.485 --> 00:06:26.901
Yes.

00:06:27.735 --> 00:06:28.735
Good morning, sir!

00:06:28.735 --> 00:06:29.485
Good morning.

00:06:29.985 --> 00:06:30.693
Let me introduce you guys.

00:06:30.776 --> 00:06:31.776
This is Sudhir...

00:06:31.901 --> 00:06:32.776
a very amiable person.

00:06:33.193 --> 00:06:34.485
He's in charge
of the Chowdhury House.

00:06:35.068 --> 00:06:37.193
This is Ayan... Ayan Sengupta.
Our director.

00:06:37.235 --> 00:06:38.068
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:06:38.318 --> 00:06:39.735
What films have you made, sir?

00:06:40.026 --> 00:06:42.235
Haven't made a feature film yet.

00:06:42.318 --> 00:06:43.401
I make ad films and stuff.

00:06:43.443 --> 00:06:44.026
Commercials.

00:06:44.026 --> 00:06:45.235
Oh, commercial films?

00:06:45.318 --> 00:06:46.860
No, ad films...

00:06:46.985 --> 00:06:48.151
The ones that come
in between TV shows.

00:06:48.151 --> 00:06:50.110
Oh... Publicity.

00:06:50.193 --> 00:06:52.110
This is Rinka,
our assistant director.

00:06:52.193 --> 00:06:53.068
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:06:54.151 --> 00:06:58.026
What a waste of such an enormous house.
Almost all of it is locked up.

00:06:58.068 --> 00:07:00.485
Just take a look inside,
the space is amazing!

00:07:00.651 --> 00:07:03.818
This house is
over 250 years old!

00:07:04.110 --> 00:07:04.943
Wow!

00:07:04.943 --> 00:07:05.901
Are ceremonies still performed here?

00:07:06.068 --> 00:07:07.485
Yeah, sort of.

00:07:07.985 --> 00:07:09.818
Used to be quite an ordeal earlier.

00:07:09.943 --> 00:07:12.485
Family members would come
from all over.

00:07:12.818 --> 00:07:15.443
Everybody would be
in festive spirits.

00:07:16.360 --> 00:07:18.901
The best artisans
would make the idols.

00:07:19.276 --> 00:07:23.235
Hundreds would feast for days.

00:07:23.651 --> 00:07:26.735
Theatre... music...
every evening!

00:07:27.026 --> 00:07:29.776
Now we do as much as we can.

00:07:29.943 --> 00:07:34.985
Otherwise, it would have been sold
a long time ago.

00:07:35.026 --> 00:07:36.860
Only if Sumit had arrived...

00:07:36.943 --> 00:07:38.693
- Are you expecting anyone else?
- Yes.

00:07:38.693 --> 00:07:40.401
Our DOP, Sumit Ray.

00:07:40.485 --> 00:07:41.485
D...DOP?

00:07:41.485 --> 00:07:42.151
Cameraman.

00:07:42.151 --> 00:07:43.735
- Oh.
- Our cameraman, Sumit Ray.

00:07:43.818 --> 00:07:46.568
What kind of place
are you really looking for?

00:07:47.110 --> 00:07:49.318
This house is quite spread out...

00:07:50.276 --> 00:07:51.443
Inner palace...

00:07:51.818 --> 00:07:52.943
Outer palace...

00:07:53.193 --> 00:07:54.026
Prayer room...

00:07:54.443 --> 00:07:57.443
- Kitchen...
- What we actually need is a verandah.

00:07:57.485 --> 00:07:57.943
Oh.

00:07:57.985 --> 00:08:02.151
It would be great
if the flooring is checkered.

00:08:02.151 --> 00:08:04.235
But it'll be great
if it's a little less run-down.

00:08:04.610 --> 00:08:09.360
You'll find it in the new palace.

00:08:09.360 --> 00:08:09.818
Great!

00:08:10.193 --> 00:08:13.360
Darpa Narayan Chowdhury had built it
to entertain English guests.

00:08:13.360 --> 00:08:13.818
Really?

00:08:13.818 --> 00:08:17.151
This old section was constructed
about 50 years before that.

00:08:18.026 --> 00:08:19.151
That's the prayer room.

00:08:19.276 --> 00:08:20.901
Come.
This way.

00:08:23.526 --> 00:08:26.110
I love wandering
around these old houses.

00:08:26.610 --> 00:08:29.068
It's rather thrilling.

00:08:30.360 --> 00:08:34.818
I would like to take a tour
of the entire house.

00:08:35.151 --> 00:08:37.693
I'm here for about an hour.

00:08:38.026 --> 00:08:40.818
- We'll cover a lot on the way up.
- Good.

00:08:41.151 --> 00:08:42.276
- Come, Rinka.
- Hmm.

00:08:48.985 --> 00:08:49.776
Watch your step.

00:08:50.735 --> 00:08:51.901
Check out the stain glass work?

00:08:51.901 --> 00:08:52.860
Yeah, it's fantastic.

00:08:52.860 --> 00:08:54.235
You won't get these nowadays.

00:08:54.526 --> 00:08:59.360
This new portion has been repaired
and painted for shooting purposes.

00:09:01.276 --> 00:09:03.860
The architecture here is quite different.

00:09:04.026 --> 00:09:04.651
Yes.

00:09:05.151 --> 00:09:12.818
These aristocratic houses are an eclectic
hotchpotch of architecture from various periods.

00:09:14.193 --> 00:09:15.568
This side is pretty interesting.

00:09:16.235 --> 00:09:18.651
- Let us take a look at that side.
- Yes, let's.

00:09:19.068 --> 00:09:21.443
- We'll take the shots here, okay?
- Okay.

00:09:21.651 --> 00:09:22.860
- Hold on to these.
- Sure.

00:09:27.318 --> 00:09:31.193
The actor will be resting
on a recliner...

00:09:32.776 --> 00:09:35.776
- Right here, okay?
- Okay.

00:09:36.860 --> 00:09:38.860
We'll get the entire depth
at the back.

00:09:38.860 --> 00:09:41.735
And the shadow of the railing pattern
on the floor will be superb!

00:09:41.776 --> 00:09:42.401
Nice.

00:09:42.401 --> 00:09:44.985
Your laptop has the script
and the storyboard.

00:09:45.026 --> 00:09:45.901
Should I switch it on?

00:09:46.276 --> 00:09:49.485
It's all stored in my head.

00:09:49.818 --> 00:09:50.901
Once Sumit gets here...

00:09:51.485 --> 00:09:53.068
we'll finalise the shot divisions.

00:09:53.318 --> 00:09:53.985
Okay.

00:09:54.276 --> 00:09:55.901
Listen, we still have 15 minutes.

00:09:56.776 --> 00:09:58.318
Let's check out the rest
of the house.

00:09:58.776 --> 00:10:00.610
You go ahead, I'll be right there.

00:10:00.818 --> 00:10:02.818
These people will do anything
for publicity!

00:10:02.818 --> 00:10:04.943
Nantu, don't gossip!

00:10:05.068 --> 00:10:05.651
Sudhir...

00:10:05.651 --> 00:10:07.651
Let's complete our "conducted tour".

00:10:07.651 --> 00:10:08.610
Yes... Let's go.

00:10:08.610 --> 00:10:10.651
Ayan, I was actually telling him
about that case.

00:10:22.443 --> 00:10:25.360
After the rumour about the ghost...

00:10:25.360 --> 00:10:27.110
people come here a lot less
to shoot films.

00:10:27.110 --> 00:10:27.901
- Oh.
- Yeah.

00:10:27.901 --> 00:10:29.610
It's good in a way.

00:10:29.610 --> 00:10:30.943
The house belongs
to 12 ghosts!

00:10:31.193 --> 00:10:33.318
Nobody gets paid directly
in any case.

00:10:33.360 --> 00:10:36.193
It's directly despoited
with the arbitrators.

00:10:36.193 --> 00:10:38.276
And that's used to pay the taxes
of this house.

00:10:38.360 --> 00:10:41.818
Are you sure
the ghost stories are rumours?

00:10:41.818 --> 00:10:45.318
There must be a few
in such an old house!

00:10:45.776 --> 00:10:47.485
- Well said!
- You don't say!

00:10:47.735 --> 00:10:49.068
It's definitely haunted.

00:10:49.485 --> 00:10:54.568
The founder of this palace
couldn't enjoy it for very long.

00:10:54.610 --> 00:10:55.193
Oh!

00:10:55.193 --> 00:10:57.151
I've heard from my ancestors...

00:10:57.151 --> 00:11:03.443
Once he had arranged
for a dance extravaganza...

00:11:03.526 --> 00:11:06.735
and was instantly titled
the "Raibahadur"

00:11:06.860 --> 00:11:07.651
Let's go.

00:11:08.068 --> 00:11:09.068
Rinka...

00:11:09.443 --> 00:11:10.610
Yes, coming.

00:11:11.693 --> 00:11:12.735
Let's check out that side first.

00:11:12.901 --> 00:11:13.943
Here, take this.

00:11:14.193 --> 00:11:16.568
You can smoke
in front of others!

00:11:16.568 --> 00:11:20.485
Don't roam around
in this haunted house!

00:11:20.485 --> 00:11:21.401
That's crap.

00:11:27.610 --> 00:11:28.943
Check out the hall.

00:11:29.110 --> 00:11:30.068
Just amazing!

00:11:31.193 --> 00:11:34.193
Is this a hall or a music room?

00:11:34.235 --> 00:11:38.693
Yes, dancers used to perform here...

00:11:39.276 --> 00:11:45.360
a lot of famous artistes.

00:11:46.485 --> 00:11:48.735
- Let's move on.
- Yes.

00:11:50.693 --> 00:11:52.985
- That matter's settled, right?
- Yeah, it's not an issue.

00:12:00.693 --> 00:12:02.985
You're yawning a lot...

00:12:02.985 --> 00:12:04.651
Were you out late last night?

00:12:05.151 --> 00:12:05.943
Not exactly...

00:12:06.943 --> 00:12:09.610
I stayed up working
on my storyline.

00:12:10.235 --> 00:12:13.776
I have a meeting with a producer tomorrow
about the feature film.

00:12:13.901 --> 00:12:15.818
Really? That's great!

00:12:15.818 --> 00:12:17.985
Don't get excited yet.

00:12:18.360 --> 00:12:19.693
Let's see if the producer likes it.

00:12:20.568 --> 00:12:22.860
You're going to make something artsy,
I'm sure.

00:12:23.193 --> 00:12:24.776
What makes you say that?

00:12:25.318 --> 00:12:29.818
Do you know what my film guru,
Satyajit Ray, has said?

00:12:30.318 --> 00:12:32.610
"Film is the highest form
of commercial art".

00:12:33.235 --> 00:12:35.985
A producer is going to spend tons
of money...

00:12:35.985 --> 00:12:40.860
I can't make an esoteric film.

00:12:41.360 --> 00:12:44.776
I want to make a film
which I'll enjoy watching myself.

00:12:44.860 --> 00:12:48.276
Ayan, how about a ghost movie?

00:12:48.401 --> 00:12:51.485
There hasn't been a good Bengali one
in ages. The public will--

00:12:51.526 --> 00:12:53.443
You've settled the money matters I hope.

00:12:53.860 --> 00:12:55.443
That won't be a problem.

00:12:55.443 --> 00:12:59.026
I've given him a lot of work before.
We go way back. Don't worry.

00:13:00.943 --> 00:13:03.485
Try and get the work done
by evening.

00:13:03.485 --> 00:13:05.943
You won't find anyone
after seven o'clock.

00:13:06.568 --> 00:13:09.735
The ghosts might be a nuisance
in the middle of the shoot!

00:13:09.735 --> 00:13:10.610
No way.

00:13:10.610 --> 00:13:13.401
We'll start real early.

00:13:14.110 --> 00:13:15.651
I just can't get Sumit
on the phone.

00:13:15.735 --> 00:13:17.193
Apparently, he's
in an unserviceable area.

00:13:17.485 --> 00:13:19.610
He should have been here by now.
Normally, he isn't late.

00:13:20.443 --> 00:13:22.776
Relax. I'll try again.

00:13:22.776 --> 00:13:23.568
Yes, try.

00:13:24.651 --> 00:13:27.776
Rinka, let's get on
with the work.

00:13:29.360 --> 00:13:31.860
We should finish the detailed list
of furniture and props.

00:13:32.901 --> 00:13:35.318
There are quite a few
antique pieces here.

00:13:35.985 --> 00:13:39.693
We need a recliner
and a marble-top coffee table...

00:13:39.943 --> 00:13:43.193
and tea in bone china cups.

00:13:44.401 --> 00:13:45.985
Talking about tea...

00:13:45.985 --> 00:13:47.943
I think we could do
with some right now.

00:13:48.651 --> 00:13:50.276
Nantu, tea break!

00:13:50.818 --> 00:13:52.568
Okay, okay.
That's alright.

00:13:54.485 --> 00:13:56.026
I got through Sumit, finally.

00:13:56.026 --> 00:13:59.193
His train was late
and there was no network coverage.

00:13:59.193 --> 00:13:59.860
Oh...

00:13:59.943 --> 00:14:05.026
Our camera man is directly coming
from an out-of-town shoot.

00:14:05.026 --> 00:14:06.026
The train is a little late.

00:14:06.026 --> 00:14:07.193
Hope you're not
in a hurry?

00:14:07.193 --> 00:14:08.443
In fact, I am.

00:14:08.485 --> 00:14:11.235
There's a hearing in the High Court
regarding this house.

00:14:11.235 --> 00:14:13.485
I've been given the
Power of Attorney.

00:14:13.526 --> 00:14:14.568
I have to go.

00:14:14.568 --> 00:14:17.485
This work is killing me!

00:14:17.860 --> 00:14:21.735
Maintaining this house is not easy!

00:14:21.901 --> 00:14:23.901
Why don't you rent it out
for TV shows?

00:14:24.193 --> 00:14:26.901
Currently, two period dramas
are being filmed.

00:14:26.901 --> 00:14:28.735
I'm handling the production
for one.

00:14:28.860 --> 00:14:31.360
Excellent pay!
Monthly contract.

00:14:31.651 --> 00:14:33.735
Who cares?

00:14:33.735 --> 00:14:35.901
I doubt this house will last very long.

00:14:35.901 --> 00:14:37.985
The promoter is just waiting
for his chance.

00:14:38.026 --> 00:14:40.901
Any day now the house
will be broken down.

00:14:41.151 --> 00:14:44.110
Weren't you saying
that this house has a story?

00:14:44.151 --> 00:14:45.235
You bet it does!

00:14:45.526 --> 00:14:47.026
A unique history.

00:14:47.151 --> 00:14:48.860
This is a cursed house...

00:14:48.860 --> 00:14:50.610
Cursed from day one.

00:14:51.151 --> 00:14:54.985
The landlord Darpa Narayan Chowdhury
had earned the title of "Raibahadur"...

00:14:55.568 --> 00:14:57.568
shortly after the Sepoy Mutiny.

00:14:57.651 --> 00:14:59.235
After 1857?

00:14:59.401 --> 00:15:00.068
Yes.

00:15:00.818 --> 00:15:02.485
On his way to collect revenue...

00:15:02.651 --> 00:15:05.068
he got killed by bandits.

00:15:06.193 --> 00:15:10.026
He could not enjoy the palace
that he had built himself.

00:15:10.235 --> 00:15:11.235
Who knows...

00:15:11.610 --> 00:15:16.276
Maybe his discontented soul roams
around the corners of this house!

00:15:17.193 --> 00:15:18.235
Jesus!

00:15:20.776 --> 00:15:22.568
Hello...
Hello?

00:15:22.693 --> 00:15:24.568
Yes, tell me...
Hello?

00:15:25.776 --> 00:15:26.568
S**t, it got disconnected.

00:15:26.610 --> 00:15:28.026
Spook call?

00:15:28.068 --> 00:15:31.068
No... Sumit was trying to call.

00:15:31.276 --> 00:15:34.068
Ayan, please change this ring tone.

00:15:35.151 --> 00:15:36.276
Man... I got so startled!

00:15:36.443 --> 00:15:36.860
Really!

00:15:36.860 --> 00:15:39.151
Such a spooky ring tone!

00:15:39.193 --> 00:15:40.068
Hmm...

00:15:40.318 --> 00:15:44.318
I would never have made films
if it were not for this spooky spirit.

00:15:45.068 --> 00:15:46.110
Do you know whose voice this is?
Satyajit Ray.

00:15:48.651 --> 00:15:50.901
Yes, Sumit, I can hear you.
Tell me.

00:15:51.276 --> 00:15:52.068
Yeah.

00:15:53.276 --> 00:15:54.110
What?

00:15:55.318 --> 00:15:56.401
Rail blockade?

00:15:57.110 --> 00:15:58.110
- Oh, s**t...
- Not again...

00:15:59.068 --> 00:15:59.943
Where?

00:16:00.693 --> 00:16:01.651
Bhringigram?

00:16:02.985 --> 00:16:04.610
Bhringigram as in Nandi-Bhringi?

00:16:05.485 --> 00:16:06.651
Against land acquisition?

00:16:06.693 --> 00:16:08.610
What do we do now?

00:16:10.026 --> 00:16:11.401
The shoot is on the day after.

00:16:11.860 --> 00:16:12.568
It won't be possible tomorrow.

00:16:12.568 --> 00:16:14.443
I have a very important meeting.

00:16:15.610 --> 00:16:17.860
You'll come by car?
Will you get one?

00:16:19.485 --> 00:16:21.568
How long will it take you?

00:16:22.943 --> 00:16:25.860
Two hours?
But we need to...

00:16:27.110 --> 00:16:29.735
Okay, I'll try
to get permission.

00:16:29.818 --> 00:16:31.943
Give me a call once you leave.

00:16:33.568 --> 00:16:37.526
Can you leave the keys
with someone?

00:16:37.985 --> 00:16:39.485
There was a security guard.

00:16:39.485 --> 00:16:41.193
But the ghosts scared his away.

00:16:41.276 --> 00:16:43.193
I'm the sole keeper now.

00:16:43.443 --> 00:16:45.318
There is a family
of heirs living behind.

00:16:45.318 --> 00:16:46.985
But they take no responsibility.

00:16:47.276 --> 00:16:51.360
The house is stuffed with antiques...
How come it's left empty?

00:16:51.485 --> 00:16:54.443
The most valuable items are actually
underneath the house.

00:16:54.526 --> 00:16:55.318
Hidden treasure?

00:16:55.360 --> 00:16:59.776
According to rumours, pitchers filled
with gold coins are planted underneath.

00:17:00.026 --> 00:17:01.360
Hidden treasure?

00:17:02.235 --> 00:17:03.151
Wow!

00:17:03.568 --> 00:17:08.943
Gold coins from the British era were discovered
while fixing the water pipes.

00:17:12.818 --> 00:17:13.610
Yes, tell me.

00:17:14.735 --> 00:17:16.610
Got it? Brilliant.

00:17:16.985 --> 00:17:17.901
Truck?

00:17:18.735 --> 00:17:19.776
Wow!

00:17:20.985 --> 00:17:22.026
Okay, come over.

00:17:22.110 --> 00:17:23.401
I'm here, waiting.

00:17:24.068 --> 00:17:26.068
Call me
if there's a problem.

00:17:26.235 --> 00:17:27.360
Okay, great.

00:17:29.110 --> 00:17:31.235
Sir, I'm sure you can understand
that we are stuck.

00:17:31.235 --> 00:17:34.818
I understand
but how can I wait?

00:17:34.943 --> 00:17:36.193
It's a court matter, you know.

00:17:36.193 --> 00:17:40.193
Could you please rely on me
and give me the keys?

00:17:40.360 --> 00:17:42.943
I'll take full responsibility
and drop it off at your place.

00:17:43.026 --> 00:17:44.193
I promise.

00:17:44.610 --> 00:17:46.651
This puts me in a real fix.

00:17:46.693 --> 00:17:51.568
Sir, we go such a long way back.
I've done so many shoots here.

00:17:51.651 --> 00:17:55.443
Sudhir, if you could be a little considerate...

00:17:55.485 --> 00:17:56.485
Sir, please!

00:17:57.151 --> 00:17:58.151
Okay, fine.

00:17:58.360 --> 00:18:03.026
Close all the doors and windows
after you are done.

00:18:03.068 --> 00:18:04.901
- Then drop off the keys at my place.
- Yes.

00:18:04.985 --> 00:18:06.693
It's a huge responsibility.

00:18:06.693 --> 00:18:08.401
Don't worry at all, sir.

00:18:08.485 --> 00:18:09.693
I'm giving you my word.

00:18:09.735 --> 00:18:11.693
I'll drop off the keys safely
at your house.

00:18:11.693 --> 00:18:12.568
Sanguine!

00:18:12.568 --> 00:18:13.943
Come, I'll explain everything to you.

00:18:14.026 --> 00:18:15.985
- This is for the front door.
- Front door.

00:18:16.443 --> 00:18:19.235
Close all the doors and windows
before leaving, okay?

00:18:19.235 --> 00:18:24.235
Don't mention anything about the shoot
if any random people come by.

00:18:24.526 --> 00:18:26.276
There are those heirs I mentioned...

00:18:26.276 --> 00:18:27.985
They are real troublemakers!

00:18:28.818 --> 00:18:30.235
No... There won't be any problems.

00:18:30.235 --> 00:18:31.610
Be rest assured.

00:18:32.151 --> 00:18:33.610
- Okay...so long.
- Yeah.

00:18:33.610 --> 00:18:35.610
- Okay, sir, thank you.
- Okay.

00:18:37.985 --> 00:18:41.193
Just like the Sikhs are known
for their fearlessness...

00:18:41.901 --> 00:18:43.943
and the Gorkhas for their loyalty...

00:18:43.943 --> 00:18:49.776
Bengalis are well-known
for troublemaking!

00:18:50.235 --> 00:18:52.401
This is why they've gone
to the dogs.

00:18:52.443 --> 00:18:53.526
Oh, s**t!

00:18:53.901 --> 00:18:56.568
I have to be
at the police station by noon.

00:18:56.568 --> 00:18:59.235
Need to get permission
for the next shoot.

00:18:59.318 --> 00:19:00.068
You get going then...

00:19:00.193 --> 00:19:00.985
Just hand me the keys.

00:19:01.401 --> 00:19:03.193
Here are the keys.

00:19:03.693 --> 00:19:05.193
- So, it's clear?
- Yes.

00:19:05.568 --> 00:19:07.235
You'll manage by yourself?

00:19:07.651 --> 00:19:08.735
Do something...

00:19:08.735 --> 00:19:10.276
You guys take the car.

00:19:10.401 --> 00:19:11.610
I'll take a cab
on my way back.

00:19:12.860 --> 00:19:15.110
It'll take me a while
to go home and come back.

00:19:15.318 --> 00:19:17.693
It's better I work
on the synopsis here.

00:19:18.068 --> 00:19:19.110
What's the story?

00:19:19.526 --> 00:19:20.651
Have I heard it?

00:19:20.985 --> 00:19:22.526
I think I told you once sketchily.

00:19:22.818 --> 00:19:24.651
It's about this guy
who plays in a band...

00:19:24.818 --> 00:19:25.651
Oh...

00:19:25.776 --> 00:19:30.193
His parents are very ambitious...
want him to become a doctor or an engineer.

00:19:30.485 --> 00:19:31.193
Yup.

00:19:31.401 --> 00:19:34.026
He... He starts taking drugs
or something like that.

00:19:34.776 --> 00:19:36.485
I've added a new angle to it.

00:19:36.985 --> 00:19:39.568
His girlfriend has a different crisis.

00:19:39.568 --> 00:19:40.485
Hey...

00:19:40.610 --> 00:19:44.068
If you start listening to the whole story,
there will be a crisis on the day of the shoot.

00:19:44.151 --> 00:19:45.943
- Come on, let's get going.
- Let's go.

00:19:45.943 --> 00:19:47.443
I have to go to the dresser.

00:19:47.485 --> 00:19:48.610
Leave this here.

00:19:49.568 --> 00:19:50.651
You...

00:19:50.693 --> 00:19:52.735
- You'll remember to take it?
- Hmm.

00:19:52.735 --> 00:19:53.860
- Sure?
- Absolutely.

00:19:54.401 --> 00:19:55.693
- By the way...
- Hmm?

00:19:56.110 --> 00:20:00.068
Won't you feel scared
all alone in this haunted house?

00:20:00.151 --> 00:20:03.943
No ghost can come near him
with rum by his side!

00:20:04.068 --> 00:20:05.151
What?

00:20:05.568 --> 00:20:08.860
I had an overnight shoot
the day before yesterday.

00:20:08.860 --> 00:20:11.276
You know I am
quite a fan of rum.

00:20:11.526 --> 00:20:13.776
So, I can't do
without a drink or two.

00:20:14.151 --> 00:20:15.318
I still have half a pint left.

00:20:15.360 --> 00:20:16.235
Do you want to keep it?

00:20:17.610 --> 00:20:19.485
You can take a quick swig
if you feel scared.

00:20:20.068 --> 00:20:21.651
I won't need it, thank you!

00:20:21.901 --> 00:20:24.110
I have some green.

00:20:24.151 --> 00:20:25.068
Oh!

00:20:25.860 --> 00:20:27.235
- Really...you guys!
- Come on, now.

00:20:27.276 --> 00:20:28.235
- Let's go.
- Bye.

00:20:28.235 --> 00:20:29.943
- Bye.
- Bye.

00:22:13.693 --> 00:22:14.443
Oh!

00:22:25.026 --> 00:22:26.568
THE BATTLE OF PLASSEY

00:22:26.568 --> 00:22:27.485
Hmm!

00:22:52.318 --> 00:22:53.401
Yes, Sumit?

00:22:53.693 --> 00:22:54.360
Where are you?

00:22:55.651 --> 00:22:56.568
Oh God...

00:22:56.651 --> 00:22:58.568
It's still a matter
of one and a half hours, then.

00:22:59.110 --> 00:23:01.026
Okay, I'll wait.

00:23:01.943 --> 00:23:03.818
This house is really interesting.

00:23:04.110 --> 00:23:06.068
I'm exploring the surroundings.

00:23:06.485 --> 00:23:08.693
You can't imagine the kind of things
that are scattered around.

00:23:09.193 --> 00:23:11.443
An old edition of "The Battle of Plassey"
by Nabinchandra Sen...

00:23:11.610 --> 00:23:16.526
a newspaper from 1971
that covers the death of a Naxalite leader...

00:23:16.943 --> 00:23:18.818
I'm in a complete time warp!

00:24:21.401 --> 00:24:22.276
Who's there?

00:24:23.860 --> 00:24:25.151
I live here.

00:24:25.276 --> 00:24:25.943
Oh.

00:24:26.360 --> 00:24:27.901
Sudhir mentioned, in fact.

00:24:27.985 --> 00:24:28.610
Huh!

00:24:28.735 --> 00:24:29.860
What does he know?

00:24:30.443 --> 00:24:31.318
How come you're here?

00:24:31.318 --> 00:24:32.026
Alone?

00:24:32.693 --> 00:24:35.151
I'm here for some work.

00:24:35.401 --> 00:24:37.568
Waiting for someone.

00:24:37.735 --> 00:24:38.568
Shooting?

00:24:39.818 --> 00:24:41.318
Yeah...

00:24:41.485 --> 00:24:43.401
So, what's your film like?

00:24:43.860 --> 00:24:45.943
Social or commercial?

00:24:46.401 --> 00:24:50.401
Or is it one of those intellectual, art films?
With messages and all!

00:24:51.568 --> 00:24:52.985
No. None of those.

00:24:53.651 --> 00:24:56.610
I was into films too,
at one point in time.

00:24:56.610 --> 00:24:57.360
Really?

00:24:57.443 --> 00:24:58.860
I was a member
of the Cine Club.

00:24:59.401 --> 00:25:01.443
Fellini, Truffaut, Bergman...

00:25:01.735 --> 00:25:04.360
And our very own Satyajit,
Ritwik, Mrinal...

00:25:04.485 --> 00:25:05.193
Just brilliant!

00:25:05.401 --> 00:25:06.526
What films they made!

00:25:06.568 --> 00:25:09.360
I see that you're a real film buff.

00:25:09.735 --> 00:25:11.276
What about contemporary film makers?

00:25:11.276 --> 00:25:14.110
Such as Wong Kar Wai,
Tarantino, Almodóvar...

00:25:14.110 --> 00:25:15.401
You must have seen their works?

00:25:16.151 --> 00:25:19.735
Unfortunately, I haven't been able
to watch films recently.

00:25:20.360 --> 00:25:21.776
So, what's your film like?

00:25:22.610 --> 00:25:24.985
Mine is merely a film
on requisition.

00:25:25.693 --> 00:25:26.568
Ad film.

00:25:27.360 --> 00:25:30.026
Oh, for advertising?

00:25:30.026 --> 00:25:30.943
Yes, indeed.

00:25:31.068 --> 00:25:32.943
Slavery of consumerism!

00:25:33.276 --> 00:25:34.485
Commodity fetishism!

00:25:35.276 --> 00:25:38.026
The entire country is now filled
with brazen bourgeoisie.

00:25:38.943 --> 00:25:41.193
You yourself mentioned Satyajit Ray...

00:25:41.610 --> 00:25:44.068
He was also
from the world of advertising.

00:25:44.651 --> 00:25:49.151
See, if we don't advertise
salt and soap, how will we survive?

00:25:49.485 --> 00:25:51.651
And who exactly will produce
my independent film?

00:25:52.276 --> 00:25:52.901
Is that so?

00:25:53.526 --> 00:25:55.360
So you actually are interested
in making a feature film.

00:25:55.526 --> 00:25:56.943
Definitely.

00:25:57.651 --> 00:25:59.318
In fact, I have a story
in mind too.

00:25:59.985 --> 00:26:01.443
It's called "Badly Bangali".

00:26:01.776 --> 00:26:04.610
In fact, I'm meeting a producer tomorrow.

00:26:05.443 --> 00:26:06.610
Great, so let's hear it!

00:26:06.901 --> 00:26:08.068
If you don't mind, of course.

00:26:08.151 --> 00:26:09.526
No, why should I mind?

00:26:10.235 --> 00:26:13.235
The basic story revolves
around a guy.

00:26:13.568 --> 00:26:15.110
The guy plays in a band...

00:26:15.485 --> 00:26:16.901
- So--
- Band?

00:26:17.651 --> 00:26:18.443
Marching band?

00:26:19.526 --> 00:26:20.068
No.

00:26:20.776 --> 00:26:23.860
Band...as in a music group.

00:26:24.818 --> 00:26:25.943
Like The Beatles?

00:26:27.318 --> 00:26:29.985
Yes, but they play Bengali music.

00:26:31.068 --> 00:26:32.735
Bengali band?

00:26:34.110 --> 00:26:35.443
Bit of an oxymoron.

00:26:35.943 --> 00:26:37.235
Interesting, carry on.

00:26:37.526 --> 00:26:38.151
Yeah...

00:26:39.610 --> 00:26:47.110
The guy's parents want to realise
their unfulfilled aspirations through their son.

00:26:47.818 --> 00:26:51.360
Now, this guy just can't relate
to any of this.

00:26:51.693 --> 00:26:55.068
He is unable to compose songs.

00:26:55.401 --> 00:26:57.943
He's in a sort of non-creative limbo.

00:26:58.568 --> 00:27:05.901
And his girlfriend's parents want
to marry her off to a well-settled guy.

00:27:07.151 --> 00:27:08.735
Old wine in a new bottle.

00:27:08.860 --> 00:27:10.068
What happens in the end?

00:27:10.860 --> 00:27:12.235
That's the problem.

00:27:12.235 --> 00:27:15.610
I just can't figure it out.

00:27:15.860 --> 00:27:19.651
I have introduced a number
of new characters...

00:27:20.526 --> 00:27:22.193
Brought in a lot
of plot points...

00:27:22.651 --> 00:27:25.318
There are crises, cinematic moments...

00:27:25.318 --> 00:27:27.651
But I can't figure out the resolution.

00:27:27.735 --> 00:27:30.068
I must come up
with something by tomorrow.

00:27:31.151 --> 00:27:34.151
I have a tremendous story
for a film.

00:27:34.443 --> 00:27:36.110
I was really into all this long ago.

00:27:36.235 --> 00:27:38.443
Try me out.
It might just work for you.

00:27:38.610 --> 00:27:39.485
Interested?

00:27:40.235 --> 00:27:41.735
Hmm, why not?

00:27:42.776 --> 00:27:46.443
A story idea is always welcome.

00:27:46.901 --> 00:27:51.026
Besides, I'm stuck here
for at least an hour and a half.

00:27:51.235 --> 00:27:53.735
What can be a better pass-time
than a story, hmm?

00:27:53.860 --> 00:27:57.943
Then let's start the story
with a smoke.

00:27:57.943 --> 00:27:59.026
Let's go.

00:27:59.401 --> 00:28:00.526
Here you go.

00:28:00.735 --> 00:28:01.860
No thanks, I have mine.

00:28:02.026 --> 00:28:05.318
But...
Do you still get that brand?

00:28:06.235 --> 00:28:09.026
The old houses of Calcutta
are vanishing rapidly.

00:28:09.651 --> 00:28:13.318
 From the two-century-old houses
of North Calcutta...

00:28:13.318 --> 00:28:16.276
to the Art Deco houses
of South Calcutta...

00:28:17.318 --> 00:28:19.276
The thrust of "progress"
has knocked them all out.

00:28:19.276 --> 00:28:23.401
From British rule to self rule,
we have now come to the rule of the promoters.

00:28:23.401 --> 00:28:26.693
They'd break down the Writer's building
to make a sever-star hotel if they could.

00:28:28.026 --> 00:28:30.735
Every day there's
a new condomonium...pandemonium!

00:28:30.985 --> 00:28:33.943
Multiplexes and shopping malls
are springing up everywhere.

00:28:34.401 --> 00:28:36.985
Only the heritage buildings...

00:28:37.193 --> 00:28:39.901
And the properties
with succession dispute are left.

00:28:40.151 --> 00:28:43.776
Although, they are very few in number
and in a run-down condition.

00:28:44.068 --> 00:28:47.193
Now the question is,
who are in trouble here?

00:28:48.318 --> 00:28:49.276
Bengalis?

00:28:49.318 --> 00:28:50.985
I mean, the middle-class Bengalis...

00:28:51.526 --> 00:28:55.318
who are being forced
to move to the outskirts?

00:28:55.443 --> 00:28:56.110
No...

00:28:56.443 --> 00:28:58.068
That problem was always there.

00:28:58.943 --> 00:29:04.276
The demolition of these old houses
has caused trouble for the spirits of the city.

00:29:04.651 --> 00:29:05.360
Hmm?

00:29:05.443 --> 00:29:06.401
- Spirits?
- Hmm.

00:29:06.901 --> 00:29:11.485
Oh, you mean the old Calcutta spirit?

00:29:11.610 --> 00:29:12.401
No, sir.

00:29:12.651 --> 00:29:15.068
By spirits, I mean ghosts.

00:29:15.193 --> 00:29:16.151
Ghost.

00:29:16.443 --> 00:29:17.401
Spirit.

00:29:17.776 --> 00:29:19.193
They are in utter ruins.

00:29:19.818 --> 00:29:21.026
Are you serious?

00:29:21.276 --> 00:29:22.235
Absolutely.

00:29:23.026 --> 00:29:26.401
All these old, abandoned houses
of Calcutta were the hub of these ghosts.

00:29:26.818 --> 00:29:27.735
Some were famous places.

00:29:28.026 --> 00:29:32.610
Like the old radio station
at Gurstin Place, the National Library, etc.

00:29:33.235 --> 00:29:36.943
These and other abandoned houses
were the refuge of the ghosts.

00:29:37.068 --> 00:29:39.776
Today, those ghosts are
in dire crisis.

00:29:39.943 --> 00:29:41.276
Today, they are homeless...

00:29:41.693 --> 00:29:46.776
moving from one haunted house
to the other.

00:29:47.193 --> 00:29:52.526
The few houses that remain are not enough
to accommodate them all.

00:29:53.651 --> 00:29:57.401
Yet, nobody seems to be bothered
during this dark hour of the ghost society.

00:29:57.485 --> 00:29:59.526
The government isn't bothered
about rehabilitating them.

00:29:59.568 --> 00:30:01.235
There are no rehabilitation packages.

00:30:01.526 --> 00:30:04.776
There are no demonstrations in protest.

00:30:04.901 --> 00:30:06.568
The politically aware are also quiet.

00:30:06.776 --> 00:30:09.901
Processions, candle light vigils...
Nothing!

00:30:10.026 --> 00:30:11.610
Ruling party, opposition...

00:30:11.651 --> 00:30:12.860
Us, them...

00:30:13.318 --> 00:30:15.193
The civil socity, the erudite...

00:30:15.568 --> 00:30:17.360
Everyone's indifferent.

00:30:17.401 --> 00:30:18.860
The media couldn't care less.

00:30:19.026 --> 00:30:19.860
Beacuse...

00:30:19.985 --> 00:30:22.068
Viewership does not depend
on ghosts.

00:30:22.693 --> 00:30:23.818
Right...

00:30:24.068 --> 00:30:26.651
Because they are not consumers
or voters.

00:30:26.651 --> 00:30:27.276
Hmm.

00:30:27.485 --> 00:30:30.901
At such a critical juncture,
the story begins.

00:30:31.151 --> 00:30:33.318
It's actually based
on this Chowdhury residency.

00:30:33.443 --> 00:30:34.068
Hmm.

00:30:34.651 --> 00:30:37.151
I sense a political satire.

00:30:37.568 --> 00:30:41.860
But I don't believe
in delivering an overt message.

00:30:41.985 --> 00:30:44.693
