There was another house like this
called Imperial Palace.

00:33:51.318 --> 00:33:53.610
It was just after the partition
of Bengal.

00:33:54.318 --> 00:33:56.860
Sir Ramsay used to stay there.

00:33:57.693 --> 00:34:00.610
The way he showed off,
one would think he was the viceroy himself!

00:34:00.610 --> 00:34:02.818
And that's precisely
what brought him down.

00:34:02.818 --> 00:34:08.735
Is the name "Ramsay",
by any chance, inspired by the Ramsay brothers?

00:34:08.735 --> 00:34:09.818
You've got it!

00:34:09.943 --> 00:34:12.735
I had seen one of their film posters
when I was at college.

00:34:12.735 --> 00:34:13.401
Mhmm.

00:34:13.401 --> 00:34:16.151
"Honeymood of the Ghosts"
with the caption...

00:34:16.151 --> 00:34:19.193
"Mountain of Corpses, Fountain of Blood,
Danger, Danger, Danger"!

00:34:24.860 --> 00:34:28.610
Sir Ramsay had gone
to the riverside for some fresh air.

00:34:28.776 --> 00:34:30.985
- Good afternoon, sir.
- Good afternoon.

00:34:31.235 --> 00:34:37.526
On that very day, Viceroy Lytton had planned
to be there in his Phaeton.

00:34:45.026 --> 00:34:50.818
Mistaking Sir Ramsay for the Viceroy,
freedom fighter Putiram Ghosh threw a bomb at him.

00:34:50.818 --> 00:34:52.443
Hail Motherland!

00:34:57.360 --> 00:34:59.693
Despite his accidental death...

00:34:59.693 --> 00:35:03.860
Sir Ramsay's ghost continued living
at the Imperial Palace flamboyantly.

00:35:03.860 --> 00:35:06.693
But his happiness did not last long.

00:35:07.318 --> 00:35:12.360
A government office was set up there.

00:35:13.110 --> 00:35:14.610
Sir Ramsay was in a deep dilemma.

00:35:15.318 --> 00:35:17.151
- Hello, Mr. Booth.
- Good morning.

00:35:17.151 --> 00:35:18.318
- Good morning.
- You've got to help me out.

00:35:18.318 --> 00:35:21.360
He got hold of his predecessor,
the ghost of Sir Booth...

00:35:21.360 --> 00:35:22.443
