of this family.

00:42:18.485 --> 00:42:21.985
Although he always looked down
upon his bourgeoisie uncle's family...

00:42:22.276 --> 00:42:25.401
he ended up in this house
after detah.

00:42:25.401 --> 00:42:29.693
And there would be frequent quarrels
between him and Darpa Narayan.

00:42:29.901 --> 00:42:31.235
Very interesting.

00:42:31.235 --> 00:42:35.276
It's not only people from various
socio-economic and ethnic backgrounds...

00:42:35.276 --> 00:42:37.026
but there are people
from different time periods too.

00:42:37.026 --> 00:42:38.693
Truly an ensemble cast.

00:42:38.735 --> 00:42:39.943
Not just them...

00:42:40.276 --> 00:42:48.568
As more old houses were razed,
more ghosts were drawn to this one.

00:42:48.818 --> 00:42:50.943
In fact, it was getting difficult
to accommodate everyone!

00:42:50.943 --> 00:42:51.901
Goodness!

00:42:51.901 --> 00:42:54.235
So, how was the accommodation crisis
of the ghosts resolved?

00:42:54.235 --> 00:42:56.318
- An interview board was set up.
- Ah!

00:42:56.318 --> 00:43:01.318
Only those who passed the interview
would be allowed to stay in the house.

00:43:01.360 --> 00:43:04.443
There were candidates
from all over the world.

00:43:04.443 --> 00:43:06.776
They spoke diverse languages
and dressed in various attires.

00:43:06.943 --> 00:43:14.943
(indistinct)

00:43:14.943 --> 00:43:17.443
Why does he constantly
keep greeting me?

00:43:17.943 --> 00:43:21.443
There's a great offer
on sub-zero fridges, sir.

00:43:22.151 --> 00:43:24.651
The sub-zero agenda
is affordable cooling.

00:43:24.985 --> 00:43:28.360
Keep this card.
I'll give you good discounts.

00:43:28.568 --> 00:43:29.568
Next!

00:43:31.693 --> 00:43:32.985
Hello, sir.

00:43:32.985 --> 00:43:35.401
I am Khaja Khan.

00:43:35.401 --> 00:43:37.985
I have fought
in the Battle of Plassey.

00:43:38.193 --> 00:43:40.360
You were a warrior?
Despite your frail frame?

00:43:40.360 --> 00:43:44.401
I was a special chef for the great monarch
of Bengal, Siraj Ud-Daulah.

00:43:44.401 --> 00:43:45.318
Wow!

00:43:45.401 --> 00:43:48.360
We'll get to feast on royal food!
Can you make kebabs?

00:43:48.360 --> 00:43:51.151
Yes, sir.
Kebabs, Biryani, Chaap, Musalam...

00:43:51.776 --> 00:43:52.860
So, how did you die?

00:43:52.860 --> 00:43:55.193
I wasn't a traitor.
I refused to side with Mir Zafar.

00:43:55.193 --> 00:43:57.401
I sacrificed my life
for my king.

00:43:57.776 --> 00:43:59.526
When everybody began
to betray...

00:43:59.526 --> 00:44:01.568
I put down my kitchen knife
and picked up the sword.

00:44:01.568 --> 00:44:04.401
I hate the British!

00:44:04.568 --> 00:44:06.568
Is he talking about us?

00:44:06.568 --> 00:44:08.776
Yeah...
Praising you!

00:44:08.776 --> 00:44:11.776
I used to live
in a palace at Murshidabad.

00:44:11.776 --> 00:44:13.735
They built a museum there...

00:44:13.818 --> 00:44:16.110
I became homeless.

00:44:16.110 --> 00:44:17.568
Let him stay.

00:44:17.568 --> 00:44:21.068
We'll get some good food.
Although, I have gastric problems.

00:44:22.526 --> 00:44:23.776
Next!

00:44:23.901 --> 00:44:25.401
My name is Shapan Dey.

00:44:25.401 --> 00:44:27.860
I was in sales
at a multinational company.

00:44:28.693 --> 00:44:30.318
You know a sales person's life...

00:44:30.318 --> 00:44:33.443
Convincing clients, reaching targets,
getting incentives...

00:44:33.735 --> 00:44:35.235
My income wasn't bad.

00:44:35.610 --> 00:44:38.985
I took a bank loan
to buy an apartment with a garage.

00:44:39.401 --> 00:44:42.235
Then of course, I had to buy a car
and pay big installments.

00:44:42.235 --> 00:44:44.068
I got three or four credit cards.

00:44:44.068 --> 00:44:47.568
My wife Ratna is a shopaholic.

00:44:47.943 --> 00:44:50.985
I would be busy with my work.
Didn't notice all that.

00:44:50.985 --> 00:44:53.943
All of a sudden,
my company began downsizing.

00:44:54.068 --> 00:44:55.235
I lost my job.

00:44:55.568 --> 00:44:57.568
I was in huge debt.

00:44:58.110 --> 00:45:04.568
The credit card company sent goons
who insulted me in front of my son.

00:45:04.568 --> 00:45:08.651
Unable to take the humiliation...
I jumped in front of a subway train.

00:45:08.651 --> 00:45:11.193
There's no credit
in keeping credit!

00:45:11.193 --> 00:45:12.735
No vacancy.

00:45:12.735 --> 00:45:13.901
Next!

00:45:14.485 --> 00:45:16.651
My name is
Bhooth Nath Bhaduri.

00:45:16.651 --> 00:45:19.776
I came from East Bengal as a refugee
after the 1942 riot.

00:45:19.776 --> 00:45:21.735
India and Pakistan weren't
yet separate countries.

00:45:21.735 --> 00:45:24.985
I built a house on Jadavpur Colony
by the railroad.

00:45:24.985 --> 00:45:27.735
I had lost all my land
and property back at home...

00:45:27.735 --> 00:45:31.235
and so, had to work as a salesman
of antacid pills on trains.

00:45:31.276 --> 00:45:33.068
I was killed
by a running train.

00:45:33.068 --> 00:45:35.943
I took shelter
on top of a tree.

00:45:36.068 --> 00:45:37.776
But I suffer from arthritis.

00:45:37.776 --> 00:45:40.026
It became really painful for me
to climb the tall tree.

00:45:40.026 --> 00:45:44.026
Besides, the trees were being chopped off
to build highways.

00:45:44.151 --> 00:45:46.235
There's no place left
for a ghost anymore!

00:45:46.360 --> 00:45:48.485
I lived as a refugee
when I was alive...

00:45:48.485 --> 00:45:50.526
Nothing's changed after death.

00:45:50.526 --> 00:45:55.693
He's a quack... It might be good
to have him around.

00:45:56.026 --> 00:45:56.943
Thank God!

00:45:57.360 --> 00:45:58.318
Next!

00:45:58.318 --> 00:46:02.818
I'm a poor man, sir. I lived
in Darbhanga district. My name is Atmaram...

00:46:02.818 --> 00:46:04.651
Atmaram Pasowan.

00:46:04.651 --> 00:46:11.401
I used to pull rickshaws in Calcutta
and would sleep on the sidewalk at night.

00:46:11.401 --> 00:46:16.026
On the English New Year's eve,
I was sleeping in my usual place...

00:46:16.026 --> 00:46:22.651
Suddenly, a rich man's son was drunk
and drove his SUV right onto the sidewalk.

00:46:22.693 --> 00:46:24.401
And instantly your spirit was set free
from your body!

00:46:24.401 --> 00:46:26.818
But how would a poor guy
like me know?

00:46:26.818 --> 00:46:30.610
The sidewalk I used to live on
was first obstructed by a sign board...

00:46:30.610 --> 00:46:32.651
and later, a flyover.

00:46:32.985 --> 00:46:38.568
I have nowhere to go, sir.

00:46:38.568 --> 00:46:41.026
We don't have our carriages here...

00:46:41.026 --> 00:46:43.360
We could get some fresh air
with him around.

00:46:43.360 --> 00:46:44.026
Yes, sir.

00:46:44.026 --> 00:46:45.110
Next!

00:46:45.443 --> 00:46:47.776
Brigadier Yudhajit Sarkar.

00:46:47.943 --> 00:46:49.360
Awarded the Dharamveer Chakra,
an Indian bravery award.

00:46:49.360 --> 00:46:50.526
Posthumous.

00:46:53.985 --> 00:46:56.068
In the year 1999...

00:46:56.526 --> 00:47:01.776
the enemy forces were continually bombing
from the other side of the LOC.

00:47:01.776 --> 00:47:06.735
We had already reclaimed a large part
of the Dras and Batalik sectors.

00:47:06.735 --> 00:47:11.485
We were carrying re-enforcements
for our troops in a convoy.

00:47:11.485 --> 00:47:14.776
Suddenly, we were shelled.

00:47:14.776 --> 00:47:18.776
I'm a martyr of the Kargil War.

00:47:19.068 --> 00:47:23.151
Later I found out that the government
was doing some scam with our coffins!

00:47:23.151 --> 00:47:27.276
I think he's the best person
to look after the security of this mansion.

00:47:27.276 --> 00:47:29.985
Hmm, these are dark times.

00:47:30.610 --> 00:47:31.610
Thank you, sir.

00:47:33.193 --> 00:47:34.485
My name is Pablo.

00:47:34.485 --> 00:47:38.193
No, not Picasso or Neruda.
Patranobis. Pablo Patranobis.

00:47:38.360 --> 00:47:39.901
Both my parents are very competitive.

00:47:39.901 --> 00:47:41.860
One's an engineer
and the other a doctor.

00:47:42.026 --> 00:47:45.526
They had tried to realise their
unfulfilled aspirations through me.

00:47:45.526 --> 00:47:46.485
Didn't work.

00:47:46.485 --> 00:47:49.485
I love music.
Had a band of my own.

00:47:49.485 --> 00:47:53.110
We had released an album too.
Only 13 CDs were sold.

00:47:53.110 --> 00:47:54.901
A lot of money was wasted.

00:47:54.901 --> 00:47:56.526
I was suffering
from serious depression.

00:47:56.526 --> 00:47:58.943
Even attempted suicide twice.

00:47:58.985 --> 00:48:01.610
Started suffering from writer's block.

00:48:01.610 --> 00:48:04.443
I couldn't write lyrics
or compose melodies.

00:48:04.818 --> 00:48:05.985
Then the usual...

00:48:05.985 --> 00:48:07.401
I started taking drugs.

00:48:07.401 --> 00:48:10.776
In small doses at first
but it gradually increased.

00:48:10.776 --> 00:48:14.651
Unknowingly, I overdosed on heroine.

00:48:15.693 --> 00:48:19.360
When the high subsided, I saw my cold body
lying flat with cotton wool stuffed in my nose.

00:48:19.360 --> 00:48:23.235
While I wrote songs about how life sucks,
life itself turned away from me!

00:48:23.943 --> 00:48:26.985
I think it would be nice
to have a musician amongst us.

00:48:26.985 --> 00:48:28.860
What do you say, Darpa?

00:48:28.860 --> 00:48:36.443
At one point, so many renowned musicians
from all over the country would perform here.

00:48:36.443 --> 00:48:38.985
This kid is a musician.
Let him stay.

00:48:38.985 --> 00:48:39.943
Thanks.

00:48:42.026 --> 00:48:43.901
Nanook, Nanook.

00:48:43.901 --> 00:48:47.151
What's this! A fur coat in this heat?
Is he mad?

00:48:47.151 --> 00:48:49.360
Nanook...

00:48:49.360 --> 00:48:50.985
"Mr. Nanook from Alaska.

00:48:50.985 --> 00:48:54.568
"The haunted igloos have all melted
due to global warming.

00:48:54.568 --> 00:48:57.110
"The Eskimos have come
to know that...

00:48:57.110 --> 00:49:00.985
"Calcutta is a dying city.
That's why he wants to stay here.

00:49:01.026 --> 00:49:02.443
I didn't understand a thing!

00:49:02.443 --> 00:49:04.151
Nanook, Nanook.

00:49:04.151 --> 00:49:06.485
No, we can't keep you here.
You stink.

00:49:06.485 --> 00:49:08.110
You'd better find a place
in the hills.

00:49:08.110 --> 00:49:10.068
Hi! My name is Koyel.

00:49:10.235 --> 00:49:14.568
You must have heard about my dad.
Famous industrialist, O.K. Dhar.

00:49:14.651 --> 00:49:19.735
From iron rod dealerships to I.T. companies,
he owns it all from hardware to software.

00:49:19.735 --> 00:49:22.735
Last year he was also honoured
with the title of "Best Bengali".

00:49:22.735 --> 00:49:24.901
And I was Daddy's darling.

00:49:24.901 --> 00:49:26.651
He spoilt me with everything.

00:49:26.651 --> 00:49:29.735
I even had a chauffeur-driven car
of my own!

00:49:30.110 --> 00:49:32.443
I had put on some weight...

00:49:32.526 --> 00:49:35.818
So I joined the gym.
That's where I met Sam.

00:49:35.818 --> 00:49:36.651
Who?

00:49:37.276 --> 00:49:39.151
- My gym instructor.
- Oh.

00:49:40.026 --> 00:49:43.568
Man, what a bod!
And really charming.

00:49:43.985 --> 00:49:47.860
I fell in love.
What wonderful moments we had!

00:49:48.860 --> 00:49:52.526
We went out for three months
after which people at home found out.

00:49:52.526 --> 00:49:55.860
That was it!
No more going out. They stopped it all.

00:49:55.860 --> 00:49:58.193
They even confiscated my mobile phone.

00:49:58.985 --> 00:50:00.276
But I was adamant.

00:50:00.276 --> 00:50:03.651
I would only marry Sam Gonzalez.

00:50:04.610 --> 00:50:07.151
They tried tempting me
with a lot of things.

00:50:07.151 --> 00:50:12.110
When nothing worked,
they made Sam disappear!

00:50:12.526 --> 00:50:16.526
I know exactly how ruthless Dad can be.

00:50:16.860 --> 00:50:19.318
They thought that's
how they would sort everything out.

00:50:19.735 --> 00:50:21.151
But they are very stupid.

00:50:21.151 --> 00:50:22.776
Stupid and heartless.

00:50:23.860 --> 00:50:28.485
But when I jumped
off the tenth floor, everyone cried a lot.

00:50:28.610 --> 00:50:29.526
God!

00:50:29.610 --> 00:50:31.693
Especially Dad.

00:50:32.151 --> 00:50:35.943
I feel really sorry
for the girl, sir.

00:50:36.401 --> 00:50:39.818
She reminds me
of my grand daughter.

00:50:39.860 --> 00:50:42.401
She died of black fever.

00:50:42.693 --> 00:50:44.735
That girl was my pet.
Let her stay.

00:50:45.276 --> 00:50:48.193
She's a charming young lady.
She must stay.

00:50:48.860 --> 00:50:50.818
The interview session ended.

00:50:50.818 --> 00:50:55.068
With such a strange ensemble of ghosts,
Chowdhury Palace became a zoo!

00:50:55.068 --> 00:50:57.651
Hey, Atmaram!
Where the hell are you?

00:50:57.651 --> 00:50:59.068
Bring out your rickshaw quickly!

00:50:59.068 --> 00:51:01.485
We have to go
to the market to buy fish.

00:51:01.485 --> 00:51:03.776
- Hey, Atmaram!
- Who is it?

00:51:03.776 --> 00:51:06.026
You are an absolute disgrace
to the society of ghosts!

00:51:06.026 --> 00:51:08.235
Sleeping at night.
Very bad!

00:51:08.235 --> 00:51:10.443
I'm not sleeping, sir.
Just resting a little.

00:51:10.443 --> 00:51:13.818
Let's go.
We have to go to the market!

00:51:14.735 --> 00:51:17.610
- To the market? This early?
- How is this early?

00:51:17.610 --> 00:51:20.193
It's the crack of dawn.
Hurry up!

00:51:20.776 --> 00:51:22.526
We'll get good Hilsa fish today.

00:51:22.526 --> 00:51:24.026
Hilsa from the Padma river!

00:51:24.026 --> 00:51:26.151
We'll steam it with mustard.

00:51:27.193 --> 00:51:29.026
What a feast!

00:51:30.776 --> 00:51:33.193
I'll eat Hilsa
after ages!

00:51:33.693 --> 00:51:35.735
A ghost going to the market
to buy fish?

00:51:35.860 --> 00:51:39.443
I've heard that they just extend their hands
and steal fish from the baskets!

00:51:39.443 --> 00:51:40.943
Why will they need to 'buy' it?

00:51:40.943 --> 00:51:43.401
They are 'Bengali' ghosts after all.

00:51:43.443 --> 00:51:44.818
Nostalgia...

00:51:44.818 --> 00:51:48.526
They have this compulsive need
to bargain with the fishmongers.

00:51:48.610 --> 00:51:50.443
- Anyway, they got the shopping done.
- Hmm.

00:51:50.443 --> 00:51:56.235
Hilsa fish, spinach, different kinds of herbs...
Everything had been arranged for!

00:51:56.693 --> 00:52:00.818
The taste of Hilsa
from my Padma River is incomparable!

00:52:00.818 --> 00:52:03.818
- Stop...you'll cross the front gate!
- Pardon, sir?

00:52:03.818 --> 00:52:06.443
Nonsense!
You lack common sense!

00:52:06.443 --> 00:52:09.068
Thank God you are now past tense!

00:52:09.068 --> 00:52:10.610
Sir, I'm a poor guy...

00:52:10.610 --> 00:52:13.443
Now take that thing out
from in between the legs.

00:52:13.443 --> 00:52:13.985
What?

00:52:13.985 --> 00:52:16.401
Oh... God...
Why are you just staring at me?

00:52:16.401 --> 00:52:18.985
Take that thing out
from between the two legs.

00:52:18.985 --> 00:52:20.318
God! No...

00:52:21.151 --> 00:52:25.068
Not your thing!
Take my shopping bag out.

00:52:25.068 --> 00:52:26.360
- Quickly!
- Yes.

00:52:27.360 --> 00:52:28.235
Okay.

00:52:28.526 --> 00:52:29.985
Now go straight up.

00:52:30.026 --> 00:52:31.943
I've gone up way before, sir.

00:52:32.860 --> 00:52:36.776
Sentimental talk, huh?
Like a Bengali romantic novelist?

00:52:37.610 --> 00:52:39.943
What I mean is the second floor.
Go to the kitchen.

00:52:40.568 --> 00:52:42.485
Doesn't understand anything.
Idiot!

00:52:42.568 --> 00:52:44.735
Let's see what I can do
with the fish and mustard--

00:52:44.735 --> 00:52:47.193
Hey! You bloody villager!

00:52:47.401 --> 00:52:50.401
You low caste man!
How dare you come up here?

00:52:50.401 --> 00:52:53.443
You are a Brahmin.
How can you give a low class guy such liberty?

00:52:53.443 --> 00:52:55.526
What about you allowing
non-Hindus into your house?

00:52:55.526 --> 00:52:58.068
All that's okay with you, huh?
Your only problem is with this guy!

00:52:58.068 --> 00:52:59.693
Biplab is right.

00:52:59.735 --> 00:53:03.276
You're still stuck
with a feudal mentality.

00:53:03.776 --> 00:53:05.651
How can you believe in caste
and creed in the 21st century?

00:53:05.651 --> 00:53:09.776
That mentor of yours, Biplab...
He never believed in God or ghosts.

00:53:09.776 --> 00:53:12.485
Look at him today;
he himself has turned into a ghost!

00:53:12.485 --> 00:53:15.526
Biplab has managed to justify ghosts
with his applied physics.

00:53:15.818 --> 00:53:18.193
He doesn't believe
in charms and amulets.

00:53:18.776 --> 00:53:20.735
And he certainly doesn't believe
in casted-based discrimination.

00:53:20.735 --> 00:53:22.235
There's a song...

00:53:22.818 --> 00:53:24.360
Stop it!

00:53:24.943 --> 00:53:27.901
A donkey's braying
sounds more pleasant!

00:53:28.693 --> 00:53:30.818
I have lost my life once...

00:53:30.818 --> 00:53:33.651
I think I'll lose it again
after listening to your music!

00:53:33.985 --> 00:53:35.735
There's nothing called culture here.

00:53:35.735 --> 00:53:38.401
That's why I don't gel with anyone
apart from Biplab.

00:53:38.401 --> 00:53:40.151
Everyone's sense of music is absolutely--

00:53:40.151 --> 00:53:42.985
What you are singing, isn't melody.
It's cacophony!

00:53:43.443 --> 00:53:45.235
If you must sing,
sing a proper song.

00:53:45.235 --> 00:53:48.610
And here I thought there would be some
Indian classical music in the house!

00:53:48.610 --> 00:53:50.151
It's the exact opposite!

00:53:50.776 --> 00:53:52.443
I had a neighbour
when I was alive.

00:53:52.443 --> 00:53:53.610
Just like you.

00:53:53.610 --> 00:53:54.860
A cranky, old man.

00:53:55.235 --> 00:53:56.985
He always objected
to our jamming sessions.

00:53:56.985 --> 00:53:57.776
Heart problem apparently...

00:53:57.776 --> 00:53:59.318
Said we were crossing the decibel limit.

00:53:59.318 --> 00:54:01.360
He had even filed a FIR.

00:54:01.360 --> 00:54:02.693
There's no relief even after death!

00:54:02.693 --> 00:54:10.443
Tell me something...
Can you sing Indian folk songs?

00:54:10.526 --> 00:54:14.776
Why do you need
to sing foreign songs?

00:54:14.818 --> 00:54:17.151
Sing patriotic songs...

00:54:17.235 --> 00:54:20.901
Perhaps the National Anthem.

00:54:20.901 --> 00:54:22.276
- National Anthem, huh?
- Yeah.

00:54:22.276 --> 00:54:24.776
You'll be shocked
to hear the remixed version!

00:54:24.776 --> 00:54:26.360
Anyway, songs don't have
a national boundary.

00:54:26.360 --> 00:54:28.610
From Santana to Sufiana...
A song is a song.

00:54:28.610 --> 00:54:30.026
One should love it all.

00:54:30.026 --> 00:54:32.735
Music is a universal language.
It's like...you know...

00:54:35.568 --> 00:54:37.943
- He's started again!
- Where the hell did he go?

00:54:37.943 --> 00:54:44.235
Are you into Western music?
I'll play some of our music.

00:54:44.235 --> 00:54:45.151
Come on.

00:54:45.151 --> 00:54:54.235
Should auld acquaintance be forgot
and never brought to mind

00:54:54.235 --> 00:55:03.276
Should auld acquaintance be forgot
and days of auld lang syne

00:55:03.276 --> 00:55:12.610
For auld lang syne, my dear
For auld lang syne

00:55:12.610 --> 00:55:23.485
We'll take a cup of kindness yet
For auld lang syne

00:55:24.568 --> 00:55:29.568
Memories of the olden days
How can they be forgotten?

00:55:29.568 --> 00:55:34.776
Oh, those good old days!

00:55:34.776 --> 00:55:38.568
How can they be forgotten?

00:55:47.026 --> 00:55:49.526
There are no shopping malls around.

00:55:49.776 --> 00:55:53.693
I want this house.
First class property!

00:55:54.068 --> 00:55:58.860
Th-This is a very disputed property, sir.
Very problematic.

00:55:58.943 --> 00:56:00.026
Problematic?

00:56:00.026 --> 00:56:02.026
What are you there for?

00:56:02.026 --> 00:56:05.360
And that lawyer is absolutely useless too.

00:56:05.360 --> 00:56:08.776
He just extorts money!
I just need this house.

00:56:08.776 --> 00:56:13.985
It'll be very risky!

00:56:13.985 --> 00:56:18.943
I don't care.
We have to get this house in six months.

00:56:25.844 --> 00:56:28.011
God! What's that smell?

00:56:28.178 --> 00:56:29.886
Eeks! It stinks!

00:56:30.094 --> 00:56:31.094
What is it?

00:56:32.428 --> 00:56:33.719
Have you ever had poppy seeds
at home?

00:56:33.719 --> 00:56:35.719
- Yeah.
- Poppy, not pasta.

00:56:35.886 --> 00:56:38.219
Potato curry with mashed poppy seeds?

00:56:38.219 --> 00:56:39.344
This is the same thing.

00:56:39.803 --> 00:56:41.636
Poppy in a different form.

00:56:42.011 --> 00:56:43.178
It stinks.

00:56:43.386 --> 00:56:46.428
You sing Bengali songs really well!

00:56:46.511 --> 00:56:51.344
- I thought you were into rock, heavy metal--
- My mom was a fan of Tagore's songs.

00:56:51.344 --> 00:56:53.511
She is the one
who introduced me to the harmonium.

00:56:53.511 --> 00:56:56.344
Can't believe you used
to play the harmonium!

00:56:56.428 --> 00:56:57.344
Yeah.

00:56:57.344 --> 00:56:59.553
Then she started pushing me
to build a career...

00:56:59.594 --> 00:57:02.303
and the harmonium ended up
in the attic!

00:57:02.344 --> 00:57:06.178
You'll get more takers of Tagore's songs here
than your kind of music.

00:57:06.219 --> 00:57:11.178
I don't give a damn
about singing Tagore's songs!

00:57:11.178 --> 00:57:12.678
For me, a song is an attitude.

00:57:12.678 --> 00:57:13.636
It's a statement.

00:57:13.886 --> 00:57:14.636
Oh please!

00:57:14.636 --> 00:57:18.011
There's nothing cool about screaming
and head banging!

00:57:18.011 --> 00:57:21.969
Totally distorted pronunciation.
Can't even figure out if it's English or Bengali.

00:57:21.969 --> 00:57:24.303
And the lyrics are absurd...

00:57:24.303 --> 00:57:26.469
"Here comes war, Budhha's laughing"

00:57:26.553 --> 00:57:29.844
How can someone write a song
about a laughing Buddha?

00:57:30.594 --> 00:57:33.636
-You won't get it with your 'Mills and Boons' head.
-Hey, I don't read 'Mills and Boons'.

00:57:33.636 --> 00:57:35.553
It's an anti-nuclear song!

00:57:35.886 --> 00:57:37.969
Atom bombs.
Anti-nuclear.

00:57:38.636 --> 00:57:39.428
Clear?

00:57:40.261 --> 00:57:41.261
Atom bomb?

00:57:41.469 --> 00:57:44.344
Couldn't find any other subject?

00:57:44.386 --> 00:57:47.803
Every song should have a
socio-political perspective.

00:57:47.886 --> 00:57:51.594
Biplab says it's important in order
to understand culture and art.

00:57:51.594 --> 00:57:52.511
Think.

00:57:52.511 --> 00:57:53.469
Pratice thinking.

00:57:53.469 --> 00:57:55.719
You're always talking
about this guy.

00:57:55.719 --> 00:57:58.469
How come I never see him?
Where's the dude?

00:57:58.469 --> 00:57:59.678
He's got a lot of work.

00:57:59.678 --> 00:58:03.136
Doesn't have time
for these petty bourgeoisie ghosts.

00:58:03.136 --> 00:58:05.386
He's roaming about
in deep, dark forests!

00:58:05.428 --> 00:58:07.219
- Like Tarzan?
- Like Gechhodada--

00:58:07.636 --> 00:58:08.803
Have you read
'Ha Ja Ba Ra La: A Nonsense Story'?

00:58:09.303 --> 00:58:10.594
He's like that elusive character
in it, Gechhodada.

00:58:10.719 --> 00:58:14.261
He's travelling all
over the country as we speak.

00:58:14.344 --> 00:58:15.594
And he likes your songs?

00:58:15.719 --> 00:58:17.928
Yes but he does not trade
in music.

00:58:18.303 --> 00:58:20.261
He trades in guns.

00:58:21.011 --> 00:58:24.428
Biplab says that "power flows
from the barrel of the gun".

00:58:25.428 --> 00:58:28.594
Whatever! Your lyrics are nonsensical.

00:58:28.719 --> 00:58:32.178
The correct phrase would be
'nonsense verse'.

00:58:32.219 --> 00:58:34.386
Lewis Carroll's "Jabberwocky" is considered
a work of genius...

00:58:34.469 --> 00:58:36.844
How come our lyrics are called gibberish?

00:58:37.636 --> 00:58:39.761
Listen to our songs carefully...

00:58:39.844 --> 00:58:42.219
Each one has an inner meaning.

00:58:52.678 --> 00:58:58.636
A tram is running here and there
Inside it sits a sad orangutan

00:59:03.553 --> 00:59:08.928
A tram is running here and there
Inside it sits a sad orangutan

00:59:09.094 --> 00:59:15.136
A scarf of deities around her neck
Angelina Jolie has come to Calcutta herself

00:59:15.261 --> 00:59:17.594
Gosh! The string tore!

00:59:18.219 --> 00:59:22.053
It's not the string's fault...
It couldn't take the sting of your lyrics!

00:59:22.136 --> 00:59:25.178
I didn't get any inner
or outer meaning of it.

00:59:25.178 --> 00:59:28.719
Why don't you write a nice, romantic song
instead of this gibberish?

00:59:28.719 --> 00:59:31.928
By the way, we don't 'write' songs...
Songs 'happen' to us.

00:59:31.928 --> 00:59:34.969
-Songs 'happen'--
-For me, the most romantic concept is revolution.

00:59:35.011 --> 00:59:37.553
I can't take the cheesy stars
and flowers bulls**t!

00:59:38.011 --> 00:59:40.136
Our love songs have to be sung
with the entire body.

00:59:40.136 --> 00:59:43.261
Our love song is passionate, uninhibited.
